WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:03.000 --> 00:00:08.500
Fried Kibbeh

00:00:08.500 --> 00:00:12.500
Preparation: 1 hour - Soaking: 30 min.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:17.000
Cooking: 10 min. Serves: 4-6

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:21.500
For the kibbeh dough

00:00:21.500 --> 00:00:25.500
400 g (2¾ cups) fine bulgur

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:30.000
200 ml (¾ cup) cold water

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:34.000
1 small onion, cut into quarters

00:00:34.000 --> 00:00:36.500
1 tsp lemon zest, grated

00:00:36.500 --> 00:00:38.500
1 sprig mint

00:00:39.000 --> 00:00:40.000
Pinch of salt

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:42.500
A pinch black pepper

00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:45.000
200 g lean lamb

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:46.000
For the filling:

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:50.500
2 tbsp vegetable oil + extra for frying

00:00:51.000 --> 00:00:54.500
2 medium onions, finely chopped

00:00:54.500 --> 00:01:00.000
400 g lean ground lamb

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:03.500
100 g (½ cup) walnut, chopped 

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.000
¼ tsp white pepper

00:01:06.000 --> 00:01:09.500
¼ tsp ground ginger

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:12.000
¼ tsp black pepper

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:14.500
¼ tsp salt

00:01:14.500 --> 00:01:18.000
Directions for the kibbeh dough

00:01:18.500 --> 00:01:24.000
Soak bulgur 30 minutes in 100 ml (1/2 cup) cold water.

00:01:24.500 --> 00:01:38.000
Add the onion, lemon zest, mint, salt and pepper to the bulgur. Place in a meat grinder and grind once.

00:01:38.000 --> 00:01:54.000
Add the meat to the bulgur and grind 2 more times. Add a little of water if necessary to facilitate the grinding. 

00:01:54.000 --> 00:01:56.500
Then knead a little with you hand.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:58.000
Directions for the filling

00:01:58.000 --> 00:02:03.000
Heat oil in a frying pan and cook the onion until soft.

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
then add the meat and cook for 5 minutes.

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:19.000
Add the salt, white pepper, black pepper and ginger and stir for a minute.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:27.000
Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the walnuts and set the filling aside to cool.

00:02:27.500 --> 00:02:29.000
Preparing the kibbeh:

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:36.500
Cut the meat into small piece of 30 g (the size of an egg) and shape them into balls.

00:02:37.000 --> 00:02:48.000
Dip your fingers into water and make a well in the center of the meatballs then enlarge the well as much as you can without making a hole. 

00:02:49.000 --> 00:03:05.000
Fill  each meatball with 1 tbsp of the filling and gently press the sides to seal the meatball. Repeat this process for all the kibbeh balls.

00:03:06.000 --> 00:03:16.000
Deep-fry the kibbeh for 4 minutes in vegetable oil at 240°C until nicely golden brown.

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:24.000
Drain well then serve.

